  "prompt": "Can I take Nyquil and Benadryl at the same time?",
  "response": "It's generally not recommended to take NyQuil and Benadryl (diphenhydramine) at the same time without consulting a healthcare professional. Both medications contain antihistamines and can lead to increased sedation, drowsiness, and other side effects when taken together. If you're considering using both medications for a specific condition or symptoms, it\u2019s best to speak with a doctor or pharmacist first to ensure it's safe for your situation.",
